Rating: 3
This is a great brunch recipe. I've made it half a dozen times. Adding a smidge of salt is important. I've never had any sticking problems, and I think this dish is rich enough not to need the extra butter. I regularly add more chile, and spread extra cheese on top. The last time I made this, I fried up some bacon and crumbled it in-- delicious!

Rating: 3
Easy. Would recommend melting about three tablespoons of butter in the bottom of the pan to prevent sticking and to richen the flavor. I skipped the chiles as my guests were notoriously finicky. I have a friend who makes a similar casserole, but uses one stick butter and two cups of low fat sour cream. My friend's version is much better though certainly more fattening!

Rating: 3
Works well for a crowd and/or picky eaters.